ized Skating Comp.|publisher=\u00d6sterreichischer Eiskunstlaufverband|accessdate=2014-12-14}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"1213 programs\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.teamunique.fi/|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6Fl4cnqAG|archivedate=2013-04-09|title=Team Unique|publisher=Helsingfors Skridskoklubb|language=Finnish|accessdate=2014-12-14}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"1314 programs\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.teamunique.fi/|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6LiOAm786|archivedate=2013-12-08|title=OHJELMAT/PROGRAMS|publisher=Team Unique|accessdate=2014-12-14}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"DOI\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.nelonen.fi/ohjelmat/dancing-on-ice/1351531-live-6-taattua-halloween-meinikia-reckless-love-olkaa-hyvat|title=LIVE 6: Taattua Halloween-meininki\u00e4: Reckless Love, olkaa hyv\u00e4t!|publisher=Nelonen|language=Finnish|date=2013-11-02|accessdate=2014-12-14}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Vartiainen\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=t7Rj0LKxnVg|title=Jenni Vartiainen - Selv\u00e4sti p\u00e4ihtynyt (Virallinen musiikkivideo)|publisher=Warner Music Finland|language=Finnish|date=2013-12-13|accessdate=2014-12-14}}</ref>\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.teamunique.fi Official website of Team Unique]\n\n{{World champions in synchronized skating}}\n{{Finnish champions in synchronized skating}}\n\n[[Category:Senior synchronized skating teams]]\n[[Category:Sports teams in Finland]]\n[[Category:Figure skating in Finland]]\n[[Category:Sports clubs in Helsinki]]\n[[Category:World Synchronized Skating Championships medalists]]\n[[Category:1993 establishments in Finland]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox synchronized skating team\n|name= Team Unique\n|image=Team Unique Cup of Berlin 2013.jpeg\n|caption=Team Unique at the [[2012&ndash;13 synchronized skating season|2013]] [[Cup of Berlin]].\n|country= {{FIN}}\n|formation_date= 1993\n|hometown=[[Helsinki]], [[Finland]]\n|discontinuation_date=\n|coach= Mirjami Penttinen\n|choreographer=Lilli Helpi\n|skating club= [[Helsingfors Skridskoklubb]]\n|level=Senior\n|worldranking=7\n|pbrankings='''7''' (''[[2014&ndash;15 synchronized skating season|2014&ndash;15]]'')<br/><!--\n-->'''5''' (''[[2013&ndash;14 synchronized skating season|2013&ndash;14]]'')<br/><!--\n-->'''1''' (''[[2012&ndash;13 synchronized skating season|2012&ndash;13]]'')<br/><!--\n-->'''7''' (''[[2011&ndash;12 synchronized skating season|2011&ndash;12]]'')<br/><!--\n-->'''3''' (''[[2010&ndash;11 synchronized skating season|2010&ndash;11]]'')<br/><!--\n-->'''6''' (''[[2009&ndash;10 synchronized skating season|2009&ndash;10]]'')<br/><!--\n-->'''2''' (''[[2008&ndash;09 synchronized skating season|2008&ndash;09]]'')<br/><!--\n-->'''3''' (''[[2007&ndash;08 synchronized skating season|2007&ndash;08]]'')<br/><!--\n-->'''3''' (''[[2006&ndash;07 synchronized skating season|2006&ndash;07]]'')<br/><!--\n-->'''10''' (''[[2005&ndash;06 synchronized skating season|2005&ndash;06]]'')\n|combined total=<!-- only scores at international ISU competitions are official best scores--> 220.28\n|combined date= [[ISU World Synchronized Skating Championships|2009 Worlds]]\n|SP score= 82.36\n|SP date= [[ISU World Synchronized Skating Championships|2009 Worlds]]\n|FS score= 139.84\n|FS date= [[French Cup (synchronized skating)|2014 French Cup]]\n|medaltemplates= <!-- see [[Template:MedalRelatedTemplates]] -->\n{{MedalCountry|{{FIN}}}}\n{{MedalSport|[[Synchronized skating]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[ISU World Synchronized Skating Championships|World Championships]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[ISU World Synchronized Skating Championships|2013 Boston]]|Synchronized skating}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[ISU World Synchronized Skating Championships|2009 Zagreb]]|Synchronized skating}}\n}}\n\n'''Team Unique''' is a senior-level [[synchronized skating]] team from [[Helsinki]], [[Finland]], representing the figure skating club [[Helsingfors Skridskoklubb]] (HSK). Established in 1993 and competing at the senior level since 1996, Team Unique are the 2013 [[ISU World Synchronized Skating Championships|world champions]], 2009 world silver medalists and the 2013 and 2016 [[Finnish Synchronized Skating Championships|Finnish champions]]. Currently, they are [[Figure skating#World standings|ranked seventh]] in the world by the [[International Skating Union]].{{r|isu-ws}} The team's home club, HSK, is also the home club to the junior team [[Team Mystique]].\n\n==History==\nTeam Unique were established in 1993 and have competed at the senior level since 1996. Until the [[2008&ndash;09 synchronized skating season|2008&ndash;09]] season, they stood out from the other Finnish top senior teams by having a few male skaters.<ref name=hsk-historia/>{{r|mtv3 Jan 26 2004}} Head-coached by Mirjami Penttinen since 2000, the team have a long history from the early 2000s of placing third behind [[Marigold IceUnity]] and [[Rockettes (synchronized skating team)|Rockettes]] at the two Finnish Championships Qualifiers and [[Finnish Synchronized Skating Championships|Finnish Championships]]. In January 2020, the Disciplinary Board of the Finnish Figure Skating Association imposed a one-year competition ban on Penttinen for violating the ethical rules of the sport. Penttinen was found to have repeatedly used inappropriate language towards her trainees, humiliated them, including urging her trainees to kill themselves.<ref>https://yle.fi/urheilu/3-11164048</ref><ref>https://www.hs.fi/urheilu/art-2000006379039.html</ref><ref>https://www.time24.news/2020/01/a-shelved-figure-skating-coach-told-yale-about-his-methods-in-2013-this-is-really-merciless.html</ref>\n\nBy placing second or first at the national competitions and so beating Rockettes, Team Unique qualified as Team Finland 2 to the [[ISU World Synchronized Skating Championships|World Championships]] in 2002, 2003 and [[2006&ndash;07 synchronized skating season|2007]], placing sixth, fourth{{r|0203 wssc}} and fifth, respectively, and in [[2008&ndash;09 synchronized skating season|2009]], earning silver.<ref name=HSKteam/>{{r|0809 wssc}} The [[2012&ndash;13 synchronized skating season|2012&ndash;13]] season was, however, historical for the team in terms of competitive results &ndash; before winning the 2013 [[ISU World Synchronized Skating Championships|World Championships]],{{r|1213 wssc}} they won [[2012 Finlandia Trophy|Finlandia Trophy]],{{r|1213 ftrophy}} the [[Cup of Berlin]],{{r|1213 berlin}} the [[French Cup (synchronized skating)|French Cup]],{{r|1213 french}} the Second Finnish Championships Qualifier{{r|1213 2q}} and the [[Finnish Synchronized Skating Championships|Finnish Championships]].{{r|1213 nats}}<ref name=YLE130224/><ref name=crit1213/> Team Unique's success continued abroad through the [[2013&ndash;14 synchronized skating season|2013&ndash;14]] season as they won [[2013 Finlandia Trophy|Finlandia Trophy]] and Leon Lurje Trophy and took their fourth straight victory at the [[French Cup (synchronized skating)|French Cup]].{{r|1314 french}}{{r|ll 1314 res}} However, they placed second at both the national Qualifiers and third at the Finnish Championships, and consequently, did not qualify for the 2014 World Championships, under the season's coefficients on the three national competitions.{{r|1314 1q}}{{r|1314 2q}}{{r|1314 nats}}{{r|1314 wssc qual}}\n\n== Programs ==\n<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.teamunique.fi/team-unique/historia/|title= History, teamunique.fi}}</ref>\n{|class=wikitable style=text-align:center\n!\n! Short program\n! Free program\n|-\n! 2019\u201320\n|\n* Bad QUE<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B3JIgKQH63Z/|title=Team Unique |website=Instagram|accessdate=12 October 2019}}</ref>\n|\n* Betrayed<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-jcnoYjxVr/|title=Team Unique |website=Instagram|accessdate=13 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! 2018\u201319\n|\n* Muzic makez me\u2026<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.facebook.com/TeamUniqueHSK/photos/a.414060555735/10155611364315736/|title=Team Unique |website=Facebook |accessdate=9 October 2018}}</re